				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Wandor</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">I currently pay about $120/wk for insurance for me and my daughters. We pay an additional $200/mo for my wife since it cost less to have her buy her own. That's about $8600 a year in insurance. That doesn't include copays, prescription costs, or deductibles. Steep price to pay, but I make pretty good money and it has not been a problem. That is until last year. By sheer bad lucky I ended up with all 3 of my daughters in the hospital at the same time. We also had over $10k in medical bills denied by insurance AFTER they had approved them. We got nailed with over $25k in medical bills and not a single one offered us reasonable terms of payment. The hospital did not even offer terms, it was either pay in full or they turned it over to an agency that charges 17% interest. This has basically resulted in near financial ruin for my family. The nice house I was easily affording before this mess is now for sale. Lucky for me the market here is still good so I should be able to sell it before the bank takes it. I would GLADLY pay another 10% in tax for UHC. Not only would it prevent future expenditures should anyone land in the hospital again, but I would be SAVING money over what I pay just in premiums.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Devil's advocate time: Why should Salgak, Torcer and Gemdiver pay for your problems? Why should it matter to them whether your kids live, die or suffer?
                  
